Date: Sat, 15 May 1999 08:07:51 -0300
From: Luiz Jacintho da Silva <luisjs@correionet.com.br>

There seems to be no conflict. The influenza season may have been deadlier,
i.e., a high case-fatality rate,. At the same time, vaccine strains where
coincidental to circulating strains, i.e., vaccinated persons where
protected, and non-vaccinated persons where exposed to a more lethal strain.
